# Maddie OS — gitignore

# macOS cruft
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
._*

# Editor cruft
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# Microsoft Office lock files (created when Word / Excel / PowerPoint has the file open)
~$*

# Local logs / temp
*.log
tmp/
temp/

# Secrets (NEVER commit credentials)
.env
.env.*
secrets.json
*.pem
*.key
!~/.ssh/maddie-os-deploy.pub  # except the public deploy key reference, not actually stored here

# Python / node artefacts if any tooling adds them
__pycache__/
*.pyc
node_modules/

# Claude Code local state that should NOT sync (memory is personal to her install)
.claude-memory/

# State files DO sync (committed):
#   .install-state.json    → tracks install progress, lets Tom see remotely
#   .last-diagnostics-run  → tracks weekly cadence
#   .last-learning-run     → tracks monthly cadence
# These are intentionally NOT in gitignore.

# OS Health log DOES sync (committed):
#   Reviews/OS Health/    → admin tier, Tom reads on pull
# Intentionally NOT in gitignore.

# CLAUDE.md symlink (Maddie-side only).
# Canonical master ruleset lives at Instructions.md (matches Tom OS sub-project naming).
# On Maddie's MacBook, install creates a symlink: CLAUDE.md → Instructions.md
# so Claude Code auto-loads the ruleset from her project root. The symlink is
# local-only and must not sync back to the repo; otherwise the repo would carry
# a CLAUDE.md and conflict with Tom OS's master CLAUDE.md when Tom works on the
# sub-folder. See [[Install]] Step 5 for the symlink-creation step.
CLAUDE.md
